    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix inconsistent error return value in CQI indication unpacking\n\n### Summary\nThe `unpack_cqi_indication_body_value` function in the NFAPI layer was returning -1 for error conditions while all other similar functions return 0. This inconsistency caused error propagation issues in the TLV unpacking mechanism.\n\nWhen processing CQI indications with more PDUs than the maximum allowed, the function would return -1, which was incorrectly interpreted as success by the `unpack_p7_tlv_list` function. This could lead to malformed CQI data being processed as valid, potentially causing incorrect scheduling decisions.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Changed return value from -1 to 0 in `unpack_cqi_indication_body_value` function when number of CQI PDUs exceeds maximum.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a gNB to send a CQI indication with more than `NFAPI_CQI_IND_MAX_PDU` PDUs\n2. Observe that the unpacking function returns -1 instead of 0\n3. Note that the error is not properly propagated up the call stack\n4. The malformed CQI data may be processed as valid, leading to incorrect scheduling\n\n"
}